eed, this man is\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":17683,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/01\/21\/umar-apostasy-riddah-murtad\/","url_meta":{"origin":35185,"position":2},"title":"Umar on Apostasy: I did not command it, I was not pleased","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 21, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Muhammad ibn al-Qari reported: A man came to Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, from Abu Musa al-Ashari. Umar asked him about the people and he informed him. Then, Umar said, \u201cDo you have any recent news?\u201d Abu Musa said, \u201cYes, a man turned back to unbelief\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":6555,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/17\/umar-converts-to-islam\/","url_meta":{"origin":35185,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Umar: The Prophet prays for Umar&#8217;s conversion","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 17, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cO Allah, strengthen Islam with one of two men whom you love more: Abu Jahl or Umar ibn al-Khattab.\u201d Ibn Umar said, \u201cThe most beloved of the two was Umar.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 3681 Grade:\u00a0Sahih\u00a0(authentic) according\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33777,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/11\/16\/minimum-valid-marriage\/","url_meta":{"origin":35185,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Nikah: Minimum legal requirements for valid marriage","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 16, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThere is no marriage unless with a guardian and two credible witnesses. Any marriage contracted with less than that is invalid. If there is a dispute, the ruler is the guardian for one without a guardian.\u201d Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":26265,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/04\/24\/umar-on-slaves-umm-walad-is-emancipated-when-her-master-dies\/","url_meta":{"origin":35185,"position":5},"title":"Umar on Slaves: Umm walad is emancipated when her master dies","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 24, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Umar reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cWhen a servant woman gives birth from her master, then he may not sell her, or bestow her, or bequeath her. He may enjoy her and she becomes free when he dies.\u201d Source: al-Muwat\u0323t\u0323a\u2019 1509 Grade:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonl